column5: Walked into a small lake deep, deep in the back woods.  First off, this pic is of a 4.2 lb looks like a Fiberglass Replica.    5.4 lb....caught on topwater... it sounded like a Beaver smacking his tail on the surface when it hit.         Nature Shots..
Beauties! They do look like replicas.
Those are some monsters ! Great job
Really nice Smallies, great colour, WTG
Wow, with that size, you can thumb them like largies. Nice!
A couple of beauties Paul    Great job mon chum    Now I know exactly where you caught the piggy   The background is very familiar
black small mouth beast! unheard of!
we should have a ripple on yhat lake..........
I just love the colour variations on smallmouth!   Interesting pic. Were you somewhere in the clay belts?
Sounds good to me. Come one come all !!
Thanx for the pix.  Beautiful scenery.  Those bass are indeed black.  Ive fished the lakes near Gogama, the wallys & perch are the blackest I've ever seeen.
Several hundred kilometers to the South East...
